        section#about.about-section.text-center.dark-bg
            .container
                h2.mb-5.text-center About the Series
                .mt-5
                    .col-lg-8.mx-auto
                        p 
                            | Have you ever seen the meme “Parked car conversations are low-key therapy sessions?” 
                            | Well this is one of the things that inspired this series. I’ve had some of my best and worst conversations in a car, 
                            | and in talking to people, that seems to be a common thing.
                        p 
                            | Car Therapy is a 6 episode web series about A down-on-her-luck college therapist who decides to drive for a ride sharing app to make ends meet during a pandemic. 
                            | On her rides, she is exposed to new people and new parts of LA and always ends up dishing advice, whether solicited or not.
                        p.pb-5
                            | Not only do we need more black stories on screen, we need to have these conversations surrounding mental health. 
                            | It is slowly breaking out of the taboo category in the black community- and I want to use my series to shed more light on it, in a comedic way. 
                            | This isn’t intended to throw textbook diagnosis around, but to have real conversations about how each character vents, reacts, or explores a different side of the human experience.
            
