                        p Jennelle Williams is a storyteller at heart, who became a multi-hyphenate (writer/director/producer, and sometimes actor!) to get her stories told. She took the leap to LA after studying film in her hometown of DC, driving across the country for her dreams. Since moving to sunny California, she has worked on several sets, starting out as a PA and working her way up to staff writer on two sitcoms. She plans on taking her own projects to the big screens; writing and developing half-hour shows and feature length films focusing on multi-generational familial, platonic, and romantic relationships from a black woman's point of view. 

